article.linkText: Sykes scores 18, leads Texas State over South Alabama 74-66
article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas -- — Davion Sykes scored 18 points to help Texas State defeat South Alabama 74-66 on Thursday night. Sykes added 11 rebounds for the Bobcats (8-14, 2-8 Sun Belt Conference). Dylan Dawson hit four 3-pointers and scored 14. Jordan Mason scored 11. The Jaguars (10-12, 3-7) were led by Tyrell Jones, who posted 16 points and two steals. Julian Margrave added nine points. Marcus Millender scored nine with five assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
